The paper deals with lower bounds on the efficacy of semidefinite programming (SDP) relaxations for combinatorial problems, which is a topic in computational complexity theory (cs.CC) and discrete mathematics (cs.DM). The paper also involves the study of polytopes and their extension complexity, which falls under computational geometry (cs.CG). Additionally, the paper discusses the connection between SDPs and sum-of-squares SDP hierarchy, which is related to machine learning (cs.LG).
